SLS 26RS-2281 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 192
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS
LEGISLATORS. Requests members of the legislature to participate in a "ride along"
experience alongside child welfare specialists.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request members of the Louisiana Legislature to participate in a "ride along"
3 experience with the Department of Children and Family Services' child welfare
4 specialists.
5 WHEREAS, child welfare specialists dedicate their professional lives to protecting
6 children, strengthening families, and promoting the safety, permanency, and well-being of
7 vulnerable youth; and
8 WHEREAS, child welfare specialists serve on the front lines of child protection by
9 responding to reports of abuse and neglect, providing critical support services, advocating
10 for children's needs, and helping families access resources necessary for stability and
11 success; and
12 WHEREAS, the work performed by child welfare specialists requires compassion,
13 integrity, resilience, and sound professional judgment in often difficult and emotionally
14 demanding circumstances; and
15 WHEREAS, child welfare specialists collaborate with educators, healthcare
16 providers, law enforcement agencies, courts, and community organizations to ensure that
17 children and families receive comprehensive care and support; and
18 WHEREAS, the contributions of child welfare specialists play a vital role in
