1 strengthening communities by promoting safe environments, reducing trauma, and helping
2 children achieve healthy and productive futures; and
3 WHEREAS, it is important to recognize and honor the dedication, sacrifice, and
4 commitment demonstrated daily by child welfare specialists across our communities; and
5 WHEREAS, being a child welfare specialist is highly demanding, in various
6 capacities such as child protection investigators, family services, or foster care workers; and
7 WHEREAS, the Legislature has demonstrated significant interest in protecting
8 Louisiana's children and the recurring concerns expressed by current and former child
9 welfare employees is of the utmost interest; and
10 WHEREAS, the best way to understand a person's situation and get a clear picture
11 of their daily experience is to "walk in their shoes"; and
12 WHEREAS, a "ride along" experience is an arranged opportunity, often used by law
13 enforcement and emergency services to allow a person to observe a professional doing their
14 job or performing a specific activity; and
15 WHEREAS, the members of the Legislature are in the unique position of not only
16 supporting child welfare specialists through legislation and through agency oversight, but
17 to truly understand all that the front-line workers do and see on any given day.
18 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
19 does hereby urge and request members of the Louisiana Legislature to participate in a "ride
20 along" experience with the Department of Children and Family Services' child welfare
21 specialists.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Children and Family Services
23 shall coordinate with legislators wishing to participate in a "ride along" experience to fully
24 understand what the child welfare specialist is responsible for at any given moment.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to each
26 member of the Louisiana Legislature via email transmission and to the secretary of the
27 Department of Children and Family Services.
